My husband and I go here every year around this time for our anniversary but last night was our last time. The building had maybe 5 tables sat and I heard the bartender talking about us being on our 3rd round. I thought If I can hear you who else can and that's not good because no one needs to know our business. Then all of the sudden this bright light was turned on above our booth. We put our empty glasses to the end of the table and noticed the server walk by twice and not ask if we needed anything. It was like we had been cut off? It was so awkward and we just decided to leave. I want to note the server was nice but it seems to be run by different management. We could have gone to a locally owned small business place but we came here. I highly doubt we'll be back because the vibe was just off putting. The photo I attached is what's been installed since COVID19 I'm guessing. If you zoom in, it looks like the board was cut yesterday and nailed to the seat. This was the first visit for both me and my mom. We both had high hopes. Unfortunately they didn't pan out that way. When we arrived there weren't too many other diners about 6 tables. We were seated right away. Our waiter came almost immediately, gave us water and bread, boy the bread was good! We decided to get the Special : 2 people dine for $49.99. For the appetizer we got the coconut shrimp, the flavor was excellent but they were luke warm. Then almost immediately our salads came out, great portion. Then within just minutes the rest of our meal came out. Our sides were asparagus, broccoli and au gratin potatoes , all luke warm except the potatoes they were cold. The salmon, shrimp and steak and tuna all had a great flavor and you could really taste the wood fire grill in the tuna and it was like cutting velvet; but again they were all luke warm, I know the tuna was suppose to be cool in the center and that's fine but the rest of the food should have been hot or at least warm. My mom is the type of person that will send food back if it isn't hot but she didn't this time. The service was great! I just think they push the food out too fast, I'm not use to having my entire meal from appetizer to main course all served within minutes of each other. Will I be back, YES! The atmosphere is great, the service is great and the food is great! Why the 3 stars, because the food was luke warm/cold and it was served too fast together.

The Corn and Crab Chowder was delicious as always and came with either 2 Alaskan Cod or 2 Bang Bang Shrimp Tacos in a lunch special!  I'm so glad I ordered one of each taco (shrimp and cod) because they were both so good - light enough for lunch but flavorful enough to savor (even with the sauce on the side)!  Recently I finally had a chance to try the brunch menu. Everything was tasty and reasonably priced. We enjoyed the Seafood Johnny Cakes, Surf-n-Turf Eggs Benedict, Oscar Omlet, and endless mimosas!  Loren and Nelson are great :)  Update: Minus 1-star because the chef or manager on duty refused to acommodate our special requests last time. We asked for the Seafood Johnny Cakes without the poached eggs and were told "that's how it comes." As a regular, I really don't appreciate that. We enjoyed sharing the Johnny Cakes as an appetizer, but I hope I can have it with scambled eggs or no eggs next time. I was also told they only have mozzarella and parmesan cheese when I asked for shredded cheddar to go with my side of grits. I find that hard to believe, but the grits turned out to be delicious as prepared. Next time I have an issue with the menu, I would appreciate if the chef or manager delivers any bad news personally instead of sending a messenger. Too much room for misinterpretation and confusion. Also, I support enough really great local restaurants that I don't need to keep going to a chain. Good food is everywhere in New Orleans.  Final Opinion: Great food, usually great service but not always.  #NuttieFoodie #Reviews #Nola #Seafood #Brunch #Lunch #Dinner
